==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thigh
<hw>Thigh</hw> <pr>(th⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>thi</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧ih</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧eh</ets>, AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧e⟦oacute⟧h</ets>; akin to OFries. <ets>thiach</ets>, D.
<ets>dij</ets>, <ets>dije</ets>, OHG. <ets>dioh</ets>, <ets>thioh</ets>,
Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧j⟦omac⟧</ets> thigh, rump, and probably to Lith.
<ets>taukas</ets> fat of animals, <ets>tukti</ets> to become fat, Russ.
<ets>tuke</ets> fat of animals. ⟦root⟧56.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The proximal segment of the hind limb between
the knee and the trunk. See <er>Femur</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The coxa, or femur, of an
insect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Thigh bone</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
femur.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thigmotactic</ent>⟦br⟧
